<paragraph blockId="31.[813,1421,1245,1609]" pageId="31" pageNumber="682">
<emphasis inLineHeading="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="682" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[813,974,1245,1269]" pageId="31" pageNumber="682">Identification.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[979,1269,1245,1269]" class="Liliopsida" family="Araceae" genus="Philodendron" kingdom="Plantae" order="Alismatales" pageId="31" pageNumber="682" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sagittifolium">
<emphasis box="[979,1269,1245,1269]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="682">Philodendron sagittifolium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a very variable
</emphasis>
species (Croat 1997). This species is distinguished mainly by having robust stems, short internodes, intact and deciduous cataphylls, rigid petioles with purple spots, coriaceous ovate-triangular blades, non-naked posterior ribs, inflorescences with green spathes exter- nally (frequently with purple spots on spathe tube), and internally reddish spathe tubes. On Cerro Pirre, this species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Croat" authorityName="Croat" box="[1050,1289,1517,1541]" class="Liliopsida" family="Araceae" genus="Philodendron" kingdom="Plantae" order="Alismatales" pageId="31" pageNumber="682" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="edenudatum">
<emphasis box="[1050,1216,1517,1541]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="682">P. edenudatum</emphasis>
Croat
</taxonomicName>
, due to the blade shape (see distinctive aspects in the notes for 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Araceae" genus="Philodendron" kingdom="Plantae" order="Alismatales" pageId="31" pageNumber="682" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="edenudatum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="682">P. edenudatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
